OL,3,CCouncil considers changing black bin
OL,4,Ccollections to once a month
OL,6,FBristol City Council's plans were
OL,7,Fobtained via a leaked document seen by
OL,8,Fthe Local Democracy Reporting Service.
OL,10,FAccording to the papers, the local
OL,11,Fauthority needs to make savings amid
OL,12,Fsoaring costs and a huge budget
OL,13,Fblackhole, as well as targeting better
OL,14,Frecycling rates.
OL,16,FThe council is launching a public
OL,17,Fconsultation on 18 November, which has
OL,18,Fyet to be announced, which will ask
OL,19,Fwhat householders think about reducing
OL,20,Fblack bin days from fortnightly to
OL,21,Fthree or four-weekly.
