OL,4,Ccollections to once a month
OL,6,FCouncillor Martin Fodor, Chair of the
OL,7,FEnvironment and Sustainability Policy
OL,8,FCommittee, said: "The council faces a
OL,9,Fsignificant challenge to ensure that
OL,10,Four city wastes less and recycles and
OL,11,Freuses more if we are to build a
OL,12,Fcleaner more sustainable Bristol.
OL,14,F"At present, we recycle just over 45
OL,15,Fpercent of our city's waste, more than
OL,16,Ftriple the rate we were recycling two
OL,17,Fdecades ago. Achieving the national
OL,18,Fgoal of recycling at least 65 percent
OL,19,Fof municipal waste by 2035 means
OL,20,Fchange needs to happen.
